structured.title: Rachel Asks Ree For Prayer Support
structured.overview: Ree (the user) has a brief phone conversation where they reassure the caller, likely passing on a message that someone can contact them directly in the afternoon if needed. After that, Rachel speaks up and, referencing an earlier place or situation, asks Ree for a favor: to pray for some people, referred to as a family team. The call centers on offering personal and spiritual support rather than scheduling or logistics.
